we conspired. She would hire some assassins and find me some weak-minded individuals and together we would brain wash them all into doing our bidding!<br><br>Far too long have the servants of Tunare been allowed to roam Norrath as they choose. Far too long have they infiltrated our lives, poisoning others with their &quot;good will&quot; and their faith. It had to stop, and what better way than to wage war on Tunare herself!<br><br>Quietly, we gathered our minions, both good and evil. The ones that would not go freely were brainwashed, for once you look into a vampire's eyes the urge to resist becomes moot. Even the mighty wizard Cinexa and Tunare's faithful priest, Melissa were powerless to stop the horde or our invasion plans. Cinexa transported many of us to the Waking Lands and from there, we entered Tunare's realm -- a savage land filled with disgusting vegetation, mythical unicorns, and brainless bears.<br><br>It was not difficult entering Tunare's domain. Her minions turned a blind eye on us as we entered and it did not take long before we began to still blood on her Holyland. One by the, we defiled her precious unicorns. One by one we skinned her bears flinging their hides around like rags. One by one set her precious Treants alight with hellfire! Yes, the blood of the fallen tasted like no other... even better than those of the Sister Island. These inhabitants were pure and that was the only reason we spared their lives. Yes, reproduce, and return to your numbers, followers of Tunare. For soon, I will hunger again and come for your blood.<br><br>And what of the Goddess herself? Where was Tunare during this reckoning? Rumors had filled the lungs the town criers. Rumors that the angry peasants of Township Rebellion had forced her into hiding the previous day. Was this just pure coincidence that she was not present to defend her homeland? Or perhaps Lord Innoruuk is keeping a watchful eye on his children? I can only speculate.<br><br>One thing is for certain, Alyssandra and I shall return to this place again. And this time, she will not hide from us. Tunare will feel my bite and she will be destroyed.  <p><img src="http://home.swbell.net/kryson/deamentia3.jpg"><br><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62848">Deamentia K`Tianna</a><br>60 Vampire</b><br><a href="http://pub72.ezboard.com/bthetwelve18946">Legendary Twelve * Stormhammer</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub72.ezboard.com/ublaydes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blaydes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Irregular</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#C7BFBF>(3/19/02 6:12:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub72.ezboard.com/fthetwelve18946frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Malediction</span><hr size=1> When bards go bad... <br>On the next Jerry Springer<br><br>/-Alyssandra-\<br>/-Angry Virtuoso-\ <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub72.ezboard.com/fthetwelve18946frm11.showNextMessage?topicID=16.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub72.ezboard.com/fthetwelve18946frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub72.ezboard.com/fthetwelve18946frm11.threadControl?topicID=16.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub72.ezboard.com/fthetwelve18946frm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=16.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br> 